ACKNOWLEDGEMENTS The CrHC appreciate the work of Dr Eija Rapinoja and Riihimäen trendi.
Funding structures No new forms of funding have been developed for the prevention and control of social problems in Finland. Current partners The CrHC is working in close cooperation with state services, municipalities, organisations, experts and with community organisations. The Better Care began a new JOE program (Joint Objective for Equality) spring 2005. This program was implemented in co-operation with the universities and in municipal settings with community groups. There will be a Women’s fund for equal participation in 2006.
Future perspectives The Commission reviews the gender gap every third year in Finland and the next study predicts that there will still be a gender gap in 2025. Future studies have a key role in keeping the focus on the group.
